verses.text_plain: Elihu also proceeded, and said,
verses.verse_html: 1Elihu also proceeded, and said,

verses.text_plain: Suffer me a little, and I will shew thee that I have yet to speak on God’s behalf.
verses.verse_html:
2Suffer me a little, and I will shew thee that I have yet to speak on God’s behalf. ▼
▼ I have…: Heb. there are yet words for God

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I have…: Heb. there are yet words for God
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I have…: Heb. there are yet words for God

verses.text_plain: I will fetch my knowledge from afar, and will ascribe righteousness to my Maker.
verses.verse_html: 3I will fetch my knowledge from afar, and will ascribe righteousness to my Maker.

verses.text_plain: For truly my words shall not be false: he that is perfect in knowledge is with thee.
verses.verse_html: 4For truly my words shall not be false: he that is perfect in knowledge is with thee.

verses.text_plain: Behold, God is mighty, and despiseth not any: he is mighty in strength and wisdom.
verses.verse_html:
5Behold, God is mighty, and despiseth not any: he is mighty in strength and wisdom. ▼
▼ wisdom: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: He preserveth not the life of the wicked: but giveth right to the poor.
verses.verse_html:
6He preserveth not the life of the wicked: but giveth right to the poor. ▼
▼ poor: or, afflicted

verses.text_plain: He withdraweth not his eyes from the righteous: but with kings are they on the throne; yea, he doth establish them for ever, and they are exalted.
verses.verse_html: 7He withdraweth not his eyes from the righteous: but with kings are they on the throne; yea, he doth establish them for ever, and they are exalted.

verses.text_plain: And if they be bound in fetters, and be holden in cords of affliction;
verses.verse_html: 8And if they be bound in fetters, and be holden in cords of affliction;

verses.text_plain: Then he sheweth them their work, and their transgressions that they have exceeded.
verses.verse_html: 9Then he sheweth them their work, and their transgressions that they have exceeded.

verses.text_plain: He openeth also their ear to discipline, and commandeth that they return from iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 10He openeth also their ear to discipline, and commandeth that they return from iniquity.

verses.text_plain: If they obey and serve him, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.
verses.verse_html: 11If they obey and serve him, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.

verses.text_plain: But if they obey not, they shall perish by the sword, and they shall die without knowledge.
verses.verse_html:
12But if they obey not, they shall perish by the sword, and they shall die without knowledge. ▼
▼ perish: Heb. pass away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ perish: Heb. pass away

verses.text_plain: But the hypocrites in heart heap up wrath: they cry not when he bindeth them.
verses.verse_html: 13But the hypocrites in heart heap up wrath: they cry not when he bindeth them.

verses.text_plain: They die in youth, and their life is among the unclean.
verses.verse_html:
14They die in youth, and their life is among the unclean. ▼
▼ They…: Heb. Their soul dieth
 , ▼
▼ unclean: or, sodomites

footnotes.body_html: ▼ They…: Heb. Their soul dieth

verses.text_plain: He delivereth the poor in his affliction, and openeth their ears in oppression.
verses.verse_html:
15He delivereth the poor in his affliction, and openeth their ears in oppression. ▼
▼ poor: or, afflicted

verses.text_plain: Even so would he have removed thee out of the strait into a broad place, where there is no straitness; and that which should be set on thy table should be full of fatness.
verses.verse_html:
16Even so would he have removed thee out of the strait into a broad place, where there is no straitness; and that which should be set on thy table should be full of fatness. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. the rest of thy table

tokens.text: Even so would he have removed
and that which should be set

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that…: Heb. the rest of thy table
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. the rest of thy table

verses.text_plain: But thou hast fulfilled the judgment of the wicked: judgment and justice take hold on thee.
verses.verse_html:
17But thou hast fulfilled the judgment of the wicked: judgment and justice take hold on thee. ▼
▼ take…: or, should uphold thee

footnotes.body_html: ▼ take…: or, should uphold thee

verses.text_plain: Because there is wrath, beware lest he take thee away with his stroke: then a great ransom cannot deliver thee.
verses.verse_html:
18Because there is wrath, beware lest he take thee away with his stroke: then a great ransom cannot deliver thee. ▼
▼ deliver…: Heb. turn thee aside

footnotes.body_html: ▼ deliver…: Heb. turn thee aside

verses.text_plain: Will he esteem thy riches? no, not gold, nor all the forces of strength.
verses.verse_html: 19Will he esteem thy riches? no, not gold, nor all the forces of strength.

verses.text_plain: Desire not the night, when people are cut off in their place.
verses.verse_html: 20Desire not the night, when people are cut off in their place.

verses.text_plain: Take heed, regard not iniquity: for this hast thou chosen rather than affliction.
verses.verse_html: 21Take heed, regard not iniquity: for this hast thou chosen rather than affliction.

verses.text_plain: Behold, God exalteth by his power: who teacheth like him?
verses.verse_html: 22Behold, God exalteth by his power: who teacheth like him?

verses.text_plain: Who hath enjoined him his way? or who can say, Thou hast wrought iniquity?
verses.verse_html: 23Who hath enjoined him his way? or who can say, Thou hast wrought iniquity?

verses.text_plain: Remember that thou magnify his work, which men behold.
verses.verse_html: 24Remember that thou magnify his work, which men behold.

verses.text_plain: Every man may see it; man may behold it afar off.
verses.verse_html: 25Every man may see it; man may behold it afar off.

verses.text_plain: Behold, God is great, and we know him not, neither can the number of his years be searched out.
verses.verse_html: 26Behold, God is great, and we know him not, neither can the number of his years be searched out.

verses.text_plain: For he maketh small the drops of water: they pour down rain according to the vapour thereof:
verses.verse_html: 27For he maketh small the drops of water: they pour down rain according to the vapour thereof:

verses.text_plain: Which the clouds do drop and distil upon man abundantly.
verses.verse_html: 28Which the clouds do drop and distil upon man abundantly.

verses.text_plain: Also can any understand the spreadings of the clouds, or the noise of his tabernacle?
verses.verse_html: 29Also can any understand the spreadings of the clouds, or the noise of his tabernacle?

verses.text_plain: Behold, he spreadeth his light upon it, and covereth the bottom of the sea.
verses.verse_html:
30Behold, he spreadeth his light upon it, and covereth the bottom of the sea. ▼
▼ bottom: Heb. roots

verses.text_plain: For by them judgeth he the people; he giveth meat in abundance.
verses.verse_html: 31For by them judgeth he the people; he giveth meat in abundance.

verses.text_plain: With clouds he covereth the light; and commandeth it not to shine by the cloud that cometh betwixt.
verses.verse_html: 32With clouds he covereth the light; and commandeth it not to shine by the cloud that cometh betwixt.

verses.text_plain: The noise thereof sheweth concerning it, the cattle also concerning the vapour.
verses.verse_html:
33The noise thereof sheweth concerning it, the cattle also concerning the vapour. ▼
▼ the vapour: Heb. that which goeth up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the vapour: Heb. that which goeth up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the vapour: Heb. that which goeth up
